## Interfaces / Contracts

```http
GET /api/admin/catalog/jobs
200 OK
[
  {
    "id": "uuid",
    "type": "IMPORT|EXPORT",
    "status": "QUEUED|PROCESSING|COMPLETED|FAILED",
    "createdAt": "2026-05-03T14:00:00Z",
    "updatedAt": "2026-05-03T14:01:00Z"
  }
]

GET /api/admin/catalog/jobs/{id}/report/diagnostics
200 OK
{
  "summary": "processed=2,succeeded=1,failed=1",
  "failedRows": 1,
  "rows": [
    {"rowNumber":2,"outcome":"FAILED","errorCode":"DUPLICATE_SLUG","errorMessage":"...","payload":"..."}
  ]
}
```

## Testing Strategy

| Layer | What to Test | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| Unit (backend/frontend) | DTO mapping and CSRF header injection rules | Service/controller unit tests and httpClient helper tests. |
| Integration | Backend endpoint contracts (`/jobs`, `/report`, `/report/diagnostics`) and CSRF enforcement on writes | Spring MockMvc with basic auth + csrf; assert content types and shapes. |
| E2E-like frontend | Dashboard fetch sequence and aligned field rendering | Vitest + mocked fetch fixtures using backend field names only. |

## Migration / Rollout
No migration required. Rollout order: (1) backend additive endpoints, (2) frontend switch to aligned DTOs, (3) enforce drift tests in CI.

